  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     Attention Mechanism
Category:    Mechanism
Definition:  Learns to focus on relevant input parts for each output
Year:        2015
Researchers: Bahdanau et al.
Applications:Machine translation, NLP, summarization
Related:     Self-attention, multi-head, cross-attention

Concept:     Constitutional AI
Category:    Alignment
Definition:  AI trained on principles via self-critique to reduce harm
Year:        2022
Researchers: Anthropic/Bai et al.
Applications:Claude safety and alignment
Related:     RLHF, harmlessness, helpfulness, honesty

Concept:     Hallucination
Category:    Problem
Definition:  LLM confidently generates plausible but incorrect information
Year:        2020
Researchers: Many researchers
Applications:AI reliability, factual QA systems
Related:     Retrieval augmentation, grounding, calibration

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Keynesian Economics
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Government fiscal policy stabilizes economy in recessions
Formula:    AD = C + I + G + NX
Economist:  John Maynard Keynes
Example:    2009 US stimulus; 2020-2021 COVID relief spending

Concept:    Inflation
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: General rise in price levels eroding purchasing power
Formula:    Inflation = (CPI_t - CPI_t-1)/CPI_t-1 x 100
Economist:  Irving Fisher
Example:    2022 US inflation hit 9.1%; Fed raised rates to combat it

Concept:    GDP
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Total value of all goods and services produced in a country annually
Formula:    GDP = C + I + G + (X-M)
Economist:  Simon Kuznets
Example:    USA GDP 2023: $27.4 trillion; China: $17.9 trillion

